<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E86FF0848F7552CFDB9FBFF" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="007606418E86FF0848F7552CFCACFD74" blockId="200.[151,1437,151,2004]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
Remarks. According to Grimaldi et al. (2002), on the basis of inclusions, 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E86FF084C1E552CFB3EFDE8" box="[1070,1179,512,536]" name="Myanmar" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
amber is from Lower Cenomanian. According to Cruikshank &amp; Ko (2003) this amber is from Upper Albian, based on ammonite/pollen. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF0848A75565FE84FD90" box="[151,289,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Burmanteon</emphasis>
Engel is very near the Neotropical genus 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF084B275565FC2AFD90" box="[791,911,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Metanteon</emphasis>
Olmi, 1984. According to Engel (2003), the differences between these two genera are the following:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E86FF0848F755BDFAEFFD3C" blockId="200.[151,1437,151,2004]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E86FF0848F755BDFE9AFD58" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[199,319,657,680]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Metanteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF0848F755BDFE9AFD58" box="[199,319,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Metanteon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: distal abscissa Rs in fore wing terminating well before anterior wing margin (i.e. marginal cell apex broadly open); media vein (M) absent; proximal prominence absent on inner surface of enlarged claw.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E86FF0848F755F5FA94FCE4" blockId="200.[151,1437,151,2004]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E86FF0848F755F5FEF4FD00" authorityName="Engel" authorityYear="2003" box="[199,337,729,752]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Burmanteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF0848F755F5FEF4FD00" box="[199,337,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Burmanteon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: distal abscissa Rs in fore wing terminating near anterior wing margin (i.e. marginal cell apex narrowly open); media vein (M) present; proximal prominence present on inner surface of enlarged claw.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E86FF0848F7540CFDB9FBFF" blockId="200.[151,1437,151,2004]" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">
However, in 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E86FF0849695433FE6CFCC7" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1833" box="[345,457,799,823]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dryinidae</taxonomicName>
the different length of distal abscissa Rs (=stigmal vein) is not a generic character; its value is only specific, as proved in many genera, such as 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF084B085468FC22FCAC" box="[824,903,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Anteon</emphasis>
Jurine, 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF084BD65469FBE5FCAC" box="[998,1088,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Dryinus</emphasis>
Latreille, etc. In addition, the proximal prominence of the enlarged claw is considered absent in 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E86FF084B915445FBBCFC70" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[929,1049,873,896]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Metanteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF084B915445FBBCFC70" box="[929,1049,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Metanteon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is present, although small (Plate 53). Probably the best distinctive character is the presence in 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E86FF084B9454A1FB8BFC54" authorityName="Engel" authorityYear="2003" box="[932,1070,909,932]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Burmanteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF084B9454A1FB8BFC54" box="[932,1070,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Burmanteon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of a strongly sclerotized Media vein (M). It is in fact fading in 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E86FF0849C1549DFDCCFC38" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[497,617,945,968]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Metanteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF0849C1549DFDCCFC38" box="[497,617,945,968]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Metanteon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Another important character regards the length of the bristles present on enlarged claw inner margin: they are shorter than greatest breadth of enlarged claw in 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E86FF084C5254F9FB7FFC1C" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[1122,1242,981,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Metanteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF084C5254F9FB7FFC1C" box="[1122,1242,981,1004]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Metanteon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Plate 53), much longer in 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E86FF08493254D5FE29FBE0" authorityName="Engel" authorityYear="2003" box="[258,396,1017,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Burmanteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E86FF08493254D5FE29FBE0" box="[258,396,1017,1040]" italics="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="201">Burmanteon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Plate 52H).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
